Aggregate cells show dim detail as TTFT ms / ITL ms for the same ctx/conc coordinate. ITL is computed from 
observed generated tokens, including streams stopped at the measurement boundary; a missing ITL means no 
stream produced at least two measured output tokens. Per-request tok/s and request latency are shown in 
separate per-cell matrices. Completion/sample counts and full request-level distributions remain in JSON 
under request_samples.
Sustained mode: client latency metrics explain request UX variance; aggregate tok/s remains the primary 
throughput signal. ITL=(last_token_time-first_token_time)/(output_tokens-1), user tok/s=1/ITL.

